1
00:00:08,925 --> 00:00:14,115
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language)

2
00:00:14,115 --> 00:00:20,032
(All characters, places, and events
in this series are entirely fictitious)

3
00:00:33,599 --> 00:00:34,112
Krit.

4
00:00:36,254 --> 00:00:37,191
I'll handle it myself.

5
00:02:14,727 --> 00:02:15,551
Are you hurt anywhere?

6
00:02:16,331 --> 00:02:17,098
I'm okay.

7
00:02:18,773 --> 00:02:19,454
And you?

8
00:02:20,505 --> 00:02:21,286
I'm fine too.

9
00:02:27,588 --> 00:02:28,369
(Wayu!)

10
00:02:29,604 --> 00:02:30,853
(Wayu!)

11
00:02:32,046 --> 00:02:35,040
- Wayu!
- Ugh!

12
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:37,610
What are you doing?

13
00:02:40,279 --> 00:02:42,252
What are you dreaming about?
Why were you puckering your lips?

14
00:02:42,479 --> 00:02:43,430
Puckering my lips?

15
00:02:43,956 --> 00:02:44,680
Me?

16
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:45,290
Yeah.

17
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:47,803
Are you nuts? Who sleeps
with their lips puckered?

18
00:02:47,936 --> 00:02:48,480
Hmph.

19
00:02:49,903 --> 00:02:50,826
What time is it?

20
00:02:53,452 --> 00:02:54,574
(How does one
become a police informant?)

21
00:02:54,574 --> 00:02:55,553
(Being a police informant means
working with the authorities)

22
00:02:55,553 --> 00:02:56,405
(to gather information
on criminal cases)

23
00:02:56,405 --> 00:02:57,512
(while keeping your identity hidden
because of the danger involved)

24
00:02:57,512 --> 00:02:58,549
(You often see examples of this)

25
00:02:58,549 --> 00:02:59,415
(in action movies)

26
00:02:59,670 --> 00:03:00,365
Darn it.

27
00:03:01,287 --> 00:03:02,067
That's true.

28
00:03:02,963 --> 00:03:03,758
What should I do now?

29
00:03:10,515 --> 00:03:11,537
What's up with you?

30
00:03:11,906 --> 00:03:14,220
Quit spacing out. Let's go home.

31
00:03:14,220 --> 00:03:14,784
Then go.

32
00:03:14,784 --> 00:03:15,712
Yeah, go home.

33
00:03:15,712 --> 00:03:16,288
Yeah.

34
00:03:16,288 --> 00:03:17,627
Looks like it's about to rain.

35
00:03:17,684 --> 00:03:22,291
=Love of Silom=

36
00:03:24,352 --> 00:03:24,928
Hey.

37
00:03:24,928 --> 00:03:26,471
Darn that Sky.

38
00:03:26,769 --> 00:03:27,947
He screwed me over last night.

39
00:03:28,384 --> 00:03:29,536
Darn it!

40
00:03:29,536 --> 00:03:30,912
He made my worlds collide.

41
00:03:31,027 --> 00:03:33,640
And then this happened.
Good thing Henry saved me.

42
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:36,450
Otherwise, I definitely
would've lost that client.

43
00:03:36,748 --> 00:03:37,699
Crap!

44
00:03:39,644 --> 00:03:41,362
Oh, hey, you guys. What's up?

45
00:03:41,844 --> 00:03:43,207
So? You want some?

46
00:03:43,207 --> 00:03:44,192
Yeah? Wanna go?

47
00:03:44,192 --> 00:03:45,067
You want some?

48
00:03:45,067 --> 00:03:46,174
- Step up, then.
- Sorry.

49
00:03:46,174 --> 00:03:47,579
- Make a move.
- Hey, hey.

50
00:03:47,579 --> 00:03:48,573
Take it.

51
00:03:48,573 --> 00:03:50,958
Ooh, sweet! Thank you.

52
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,051
Kept it just for you.

53
00:03:52,051 --> 00:03:52,888
You know me well.

54
00:03:52,888 --> 00:03:53,856
The most.

55
00:03:53,856 --> 00:03:54,496
Hmm.

56
00:03:54,496 --> 00:03:55,387
It's raining.

57
00:03:55,387 --> 00:03:57,033
Be careful in weather like this.

58
00:03:57,088 --> 00:03:57,600
Yeah.

59
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,176
Hey!

60
00:03:58,694 --> 00:04:01,278
Lately, there've been some odd rumors
going around.

61
00:04:01,860 --> 00:04:04,486
They say bar hosts have suddenly
been going missing.

62
00:04:05,593 --> 00:04:07,112
And not in the usual way.

63
00:04:07,842 --> 00:04:09,502
They just vanish without a trace...

64
00:04:10,292 --> 00:04:13,528
Maybe they were sold. Or killed.

65
00:04:14,432 --> 00:04:15,328
Sigh.

66
00:04:16,098 --> 00:04:18,596
Come on, uncle, I don't think
they've disappeared.

67
00:04:18,596 --> 00:04:22,697
Those guys probably got partners,
or maybe they just quit.

68
00:04:22,869 --> 00:04:24,472
You never know.

69
00:04:25,055 --> 00:04:26,616
You guys better be careful.

70
00:04:26,787 --> 00:04:29,881
Don't go down deserted alleys alone
if you can help it.

71
00:04:30,804 --> 00:04:31,641
Got it?

72
00:04:31,925 --> 00:04:32,564
Got it.

73
00:04:32,832 --> 00:04:33,408
Yeah.

74
00:04:33,696 --> 00:04:34,336
Hey!

75
00:04:34,949 --> 00:04:37,348
Speaking of cigarettes,
where's the lighter?

76
00:04:37,433 --> 00:04:38,597
- Got one?
- Yeah, here.

77
00:04:38,938 --> 00:04:41,607
- You know me too well.
- I've got the fire.

78
00:04:42,898 --> 00:04:45,368
(So, made up your mind yet?)

79
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:46,432
- Want.
- Hmm.

80
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:53,024
(Captain Kritsadawut Siriwatmontri,
Deputy Inspector of Investigation)

81
00:04:56,143 --> 00:04:56,753
Yes, sir.

82
00:04:58,031 --> 00:05:00,017
Could you look up
some daycare options for me?

83
00:05:00,841 --> 00:05:03,892
I'm looking for places
with excellent child psychologists.

84
00:05:04,475 --> 00:05:05,753
Price isn't an issue.

85
00:05:06,235 --> 00:05:08,123
Just find me 3-4 good options.

86
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:10,026
Daycare, sir?

87
00:05:11,076 --> 00:05:12,524
Which case is this for, Captain?

88
00:05:14,838 --> 00:05:18,032
Come on, just do what I asked.

89
00:05:18,642 --> 00:05:20,104
I need it urgently. Thanks a lot.

90
00:05:20,402 --> 00:05:20,942
Yes, sir.

91
00:05:22,659 --> 00:05:24,193
Uh, Captain...

92
00:05:24,193 --> 00:05:27,571
I've been meaning to ask,
who's our team's informant?

93
00:05:28,125 --> 00:05:31,134
I don't have any intel on that.
I'll look into it.

94
00:05:32,823 --> 00:05:34,867
No, I'll handle it myself.

95
00:05:35,535 --> 00:05:36,770
Just get me the daycare information.

96
00:05:37,607 --> 00:05:38,317
Yes, sir.

97
00:05:49,773 --> 00:05:56,736
(So, made up your mind yet?)

98
00:06:17,553 --> 00:06:18,731
I'm back.

99
00:06:21,102 --> 00:06:22,450
Oh, Singto.

100
00:06:35,354 --> 00:06:36,220
Let's see...

101
00:06:38,272 --> 00:06:38,880
Oops.

102
00:06:39,414 --> 00:06:40,890
Why are you all messy, sweetheart?

103
00:06:47,022 --> 00:06:47,831
Mom.

104
00:06:50,273 --> 00:06:51,025
Mom.

105
00:06:52,431 --> 00:06:53,325
Mom.

106
00:06:53,536 --> 00:06:54,063
Oh!

107
00:06:54,063 --> 00:06:56,803
Why are you yelling so much?

108
00:06:59,552 --> 00:07:00,256
Ow!

109
00:07:00,905 --> 00:07:03,787
Mom, mom.

110
00:07:03,915 --> 00:07:04,994
What?

111
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:06,995
Why weren't you watching Singto?

112
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:09,494
Why'd you let him eat
a whole bag of chocolate?

113
00:07:09,508 --> 00:07:12,163
He ate it himself. You were the one
who bought it for him.

114
00:07:12,832 --> 00:07:13,344
Come on.

115
00:07:13,837 --> 00:07:15,498
But you're the adult here, Mom.

116
00:07:15,498 --> 00:07:18,181
Why weren't you watching him?
He's just a kid.

117
00:07:18,990 --> 00:07:19,941
Darn it.

118
00:07:22,383 --> 00:07:23,859
What are you doing? Give me that.

119
00:07:23,859 --> 00:07:24,895
- Give it here.
- Mom.

120
00:07:24,895 --> 00:07:26,500
- Give it back.
- Mom.

121
00:07:28,128 --> 00:07:29,632
(Gambling is illegal)

122
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:30,659
Give it here.

123
00:07:31,312 --> 00:07:33,867
So this is why you're not watching
Singto but playing this stupid game?

124
00:07:36,081 --> 00:07:36,992
Do you even feel anything at all?

125
00:07:36,992 --> 00:07:38,991
What about you? Do you feel anything?

126
00:07:39,403 --> 00:07:42,285
If you didn't have to raise him,
you'd have money left to spend.

127
00:07:42,285 --> 00:07:44,144
You'll have enough
to complete your studies.

128
00:07:45,507 --> 00:07:46,770
How can you say that, Mom?

129
00:07:47,097 --> 00:07:48,843
- Singto is our nephew, Mom.
- Give it to me.

130
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:53,258
Big deal. He's a grandkid. So?

131
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:56,139
You're not ready to raise him.
I'm not either.

132
00:07:56,381 --> 00:07:58,113
Even his real mom isn't raising him.

133
00:07:58,808 --> 00:08:00,866
I'm sending him to live
with his uncle in Kamphaeng Phet.

134
00:08:01,150 --> 00:08:04,444
No, Mom. You can't just give Singto
away for someone else to raise.

135
00:08:04,444 --> 00:08:06,445
They're not someone else.
They're family.

136
00:08:08,518 --> 00:08:12,052
Mom, he can't even keep his own head
above water.

137
00:08:12,322 --> 00:08:14,338
He's an alcoholic and a womanizer.

138
00:08:14,338 --> 00:08:14,977
Huh?

139
00:08:14,977 --> 00:08:17,276
How is he supposed to raise Singto?
Who's going to look after him?

140
00:08:17,489 --> 00:08:19,051
And you think things are fine now?

141
00:08:20,726 --> 00:08:23,082
Are you sure you'll raise him well?

142
00:08:24,871 --> 00:08:26,446
It's better than his uncle
raising him, Mom.

143
00:08:28,672 --> 00:08:29,280
Oh, wow!

144
00:08:30,208 --> 00:08:33,331
Mom, if you won't raise him, I will.

145
00:08:33,331 --> 00:08:34,722
Fine, you go ahead and raise him.

146
00:08:56,952 --> 00:08:58,414
Come here, Singto.

147
00:08:59,252 --> 00:09:02,786
You need to brush up and down.

148
00:09:05,469 --> 00:09:07,116
Okay, rinse your mouth now.

149
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:08,832
There you go.

150
00:09:10,282 --> 00:09:11,062
Spit it out.

151
00:09:14,228 --> 00:09:15,491
Listen to Daddy, Singto.

152
00:09:16,811 --> 00:09:19,324
If Daddy's not here, you need to brush
your teeth by yourself, okay?

153
00:09:20,289 --> 00:09:22,149
Got it? Can you do that?

154
00:09:25,632 --> 00:09:26,432
Singto.

155
00:09:27,808 --> 00:09:31,006
How about staying with Anne today, okay?

156
00:09:31,773 --> 00:09:33,079
Go stay with Anne for now, okay?

157
00:09:33,576 --> 00:09:36,884
If you don't go stay with Anne today,

158
00:09:36,884 --> 00:09:39,552
you'll end up watching Daddy sleep.

159
00:09:39,851 --> 00:09:42,108
Right? Is that okay?

160
00:09:42,448 --> 00:09:43,996
I'll come get you as soon as I'm done.

161
00:09:44,521 --> 00:09:45,259
Okay?

162
00:09:46,432 --> 00:09:48,608
There, there.

163
00:09:49,376 --> 00:09:50,688
Here you go.

164
00:09:52,832 --> 00:09:53,536
Wow.

165
00:10:03,528 --> 00:10:05,600
Anne? Anne?

166
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,368
Yeah?

167
00:10:07,424 --> 00:10:08,000
Oh.

168
00:10:08,951 --> 00:10:10,044
What is it, sweetie?

169
00:10:10,740 --> 00:10:12,755
Please look after Singto for me.

170
00:10:13,408 --> 00:10:14,175
Come here, sweetheart.

171
00:10:15,552 --> 00:10:16,640
Mm, come here.

172
00:10:16,844 --> 00:10:19,541
Sweetie, don't forget
last month's childcare.

173
00:10:20,847 --> 00:10:24,509
Sure. I'll take care of it
in the next day or two.

174
00:10:24,509 --> 00:10:25,630
(Childcare, Anne)

175
00:10:25,630 --> 00:10:27,093
- Sorry about that.
- It's fine.

176
00:10:27,648 --> 00:10:28,186
Right.

177
00:10:28,186 --> 00:10:32,572
Wayu, I really think you should take
Singto to a doctor.

178
00:10:32,955 --> 00:10:36,149
He doesn't talk, and he barely
reacts to anything.

179
00:10:38,633 --> 00:10:40,064
Alright. Thank you so much.

180
00:10:40,096 --> 00:10:40,608
Okay.

181
00:10:40,834 --> 00:10:42,892
Please take care of him. Bye-bye.

182
00:10:42,892 --> 00:10:43,871
Come on.

183
00:10:59,373 --> 00:11:01,970
(Can we meet today?)

184
00:11:01,970 --> 00:11:04,767
(How about 5 PM?)

185
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:12,219
(Sounds good. There's something
I want to talk about.)

186
00:11:12,219 --> 00:11:14,717
(See you at 5 PM.)

187
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:19,968
(Set wake-up call)

188
00:11:51,616 --> 00:11:52,672
(Is My Heart Fluttering Because of
Baking Soda or Because of You?)

189
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:55,402
(Hey, Get Me Some Glasses)

190
00:11:55,402 --> 00:12:01,733
♪I wish I could see clearly,
just a little more than this♪

191
00:12:01,733 --> 00:12:07,908
♪So I won't have to keep
on secretly hoping like this♪

192
00:12:07,908 --> 00:12:14,154
♪Won't you make it clear?
You've been so good to me♪

193
00:12:14,154 --> 00:12:19,690
♪Are you the one who's unclear,
or am I just seeing things wrong?♪

194
00:12:21,152 --> 00:12:24,000
♪More than, more than this♪

195
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:27,264
♪More than, more than this♪

196
00:12:27,264 --> 00:12:32,128
♪More than this♪

197
00:12:43,339 --> 00:12:44,106
Wayu.

198
00:12:55,456 --> 00:12:56,608
Ouch!

199
00:12:57,308 --> 00:12:58,117
Krit.

200
00:12:58,557 --> 00:13:01,282
Meeting somewhere this secluded,
I thought you were going to kill me.

201
00:13:03,937 --> 00:13:06,719
That's detective life.
You'll get used to it.

202
00:13:08,110 --> 00:13:08,934
Get used to what?

203
00:13:09,658 --> 00:13:11,290
I haven't agreed to anything yet.

204
00:13:14,754 --> 00:13:16,031
Well, since I'm already here...

205
00:13:16,812 --> 00:13:18,672
- I'll just get straight to the point.
- Wait.

206
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:22,944
Let me speak first.

207
00:13:32,413 --> 00:13:35,990
The daycare here is ideal for kids
with developmental delays.

208
00:13:37,154 --> 00:13:40,659
I already enrolled your nephew.
He can start right away.

209
00:13:41,427 --> 00:13:44,365
Now you don't have to worry
about him anymore.

210
00:13:49,106 --> 00:13:51,049
So, would you be my informant?

211
00:13:57,056 --> 00:13:58,333
You came prepared.

212
00:14:01,172 --> 00:14:02,535
So it'd be fair.

213
00:14:03,131 --> 00:14:04,366
Think it over carefully.

214
00:14:05,147 --> 00:14:06,751
Your nephew's growing up every day.

215
00:14:07,674 --> 00:14:11,308
If he doesn't get treatment now,
it's only going to get harder.

216
00:14:11,663 --> 00:14:13,153
Now it's up to you

217
00:14:13,820 --> 00:14:15,836
to decide what kind of future

218
00:14:16,148 --> 00:14:17,327
your nephew will have.

219
00:14:32,388 --> 00:14:33,296
Alright.

220
00:14:35,312 --> 00:14:37,072
Fine. I'll be your informant.

221
00:14:37,981 --> 00:14:39,173
But I do have one condition.

222
00:14:41,430 --> 00:14:42,409
What condition?

223
00:14:43,347 --> 00:14:46,129
You'll cover all the daycare expenses,

224
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:50,019
including the psychologist
who'll be treating Singto.

225
00:14:50,345 --> 00:14:51,424
Can you do that?

226
00:14:54,078 --> 00:14:54,888
Of course.

227
00:14:55,157 --> 00:14:57,358
If that's all, I can definitely do it.

228
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:03,703
Okay.

229
00:15:10,843 --> 00:15:12,007
You don't need to worry.

230
00:15:12,873 --> 00:15:15,102
There are child development specialists
on staff here.

231
00:15:15,371 --> 00:15:17,217
Singto will definitely get
the special care he needs.

232
00:15:18,069 --> 00:15:19,942
Thank you for keeping your word.

233
00:15:20,070 --> 00:15:22,313
You may not be thanking me after this.

234
00:15:23,264 --> 00:15:26,018
This detective work
isn't like in the movies.

235
00:15:28,772 --> 00:15:30,731
Tell me, what do I need to do?

236
00:15:31,242 --> 00:15:32,207
I'm ready.

237
00:15:32,988 --> 00:15:33,783
First,

238
00:15:34,762 --> 00:15:36,423
you have to dedicate all your time

239
00:15:36,423 --> 00:15:38,098
left over from your bar host work to me.

240
00:15:39,688 --> 00:15:41,704
You can't take on
any more part-time jobs.

241
00:15:43,137 --> 00:15:45,352
But I really need to work out.

242
00:15:45,352 --> 00:15:47,538
My looks are how I make a living.

243
00:15:47,779 --> 00:15:48,716
Don't worry.

244
00:15:48,943 --> 00:15:51,995
With me, you'll definitely
get a workout.

245
00:15:53,954 --> 00:15:55,204
As for the second point,

246
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,191
while you're working,

247
00:15:57,872 --> 00:15:59,987
you need to check inside
and outside the club

248
00:16:00,186 --> 00:16:01,819
to see if anything's unusual.

249
00:16:02,287 --> 00:16:03,763
If there is, notify me immediately.

250
00:16:06,844 --> 00:16:07,596
Understood.

251
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:25,088
Oops.

252
00:16:25,088 --> 00:16:25,837
Oh!

253
00:16:25,837 --> 00:16:27,001
Did I startle you?

254
00:16:27,584 --> 00:16:28,096
Ah.

255
00:16:28,108 --> 00:16:29,585
You're new here, aren't you?

256
00:16:30,493 --> 00:16:31,757
I've been at it for a while.

257
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:37,023
But for some reason,
now that I've met you...

258
00:16:37,265 --> 00:16:38,698
I feel lost.

259
00:16:39,990 --> 00:16:42,317
Speaking of which, Wayu.

260
00:16:43,936 --> 00:16:45,157
Well then...

261
00:16:46,236 --> 00:16:47,854
Why don't you finish your drink for me?

262
00:16:51,176 --> 00:16:52,680
- How about this?
- Hmm?

263
00:16:54,086 --> 00:16:55,775
I say we play a game.

264
00:16:58,813 --> 00:17:00,090
Whoever loses,

265
00:17:00,729 --> 00:17:01,609
finish their drink.

266
00:17:03,455 --> 00:17:04,633
Shall we start?

267
00:17:06,365 --> 00:17:07,004
Come on.

268
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:08,608
Ferris wheel one.

269
00:17:08,608 --> 00:17:10,283
Alright, here we go.

270
00:17:10,283 --> 00:17:10,978
Come on.

271
00:17:11,376 --> 00:17:13,363
Here we go.

272
00:17:15,392 --> 00:17:16,064
Hup.

273
00:17:18,133 --> 00:17:19,822
Go ahead, Wayu.

274
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:22,080
Hup.

275
00:17:22,931 --> 00:17:23,680
Shall we continue?

276
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,288
Come on.

277
00:17:40,788 --> 00:17:42,733
You drink well, Wayu.

278
00:17:45,312 --> 00:17:46,176
Whoops.

279
00:17:55,296 --> 00:17:55,872
Ooh.

280
00:17:56,957 --> 00:17:59,214
I'm on a roll today, Wayu.

281
00:17:59,214 --> 00:18:00,307
Go ahead.

282
00:18:02,208 --> 00:18:02,880
Ouch!

283
00:18:03,345 --> 00:18:04,509
Shall we continue?

284
00:18:05,488 --> 00:18:07,291
Just give me a sec before we continue.

285
00:18:07,291 --> 00:18:10,059
Can I go to the restroom for a sec
and then come back to play?

286
00:18:11,166 --> 00:18:12,146
Alright.

287
00:18:18,009 --> 00:18:19,499
Don't get drunk, Wayu.

288
00:18:27,616 --> 00:18:28,224
Go.

289
00:18:29,876 --> 00:18:32,772
See you later, bye.

290
00:18:35,584 --> 00:18:36,224
There!

291
00:18:36,736 --> 00:18:37,385
Ouch!

292
00:18:37,385 --> 00:18:38,407
Wayu.

293
00:18:38,407 --> 00:18:40,735
- I miss you terribly.
- I miss you too.

294
00:18:40,735 --> 00:18:41,488
So, what do you want to do?

295
00:18:41,488 --> 00:18:43,745
Do you want to keep playing
rock-paper-scissors,

296
00:18:43,816 --> 00:18:45,619
or play another game instead?

297
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:50,885
I think we should play something else.

298
00:18:50,885 --> 00:18:53,028
Poor Wayu might not be able to take it.

299
00:18:54,334 --> 00:18:55,981
Let me tell you something.

300
00:18:55,981 --> 00:18:58,423
I usually win every time.

301
00:18:58,423 --> 00:18:59,998
But today, I don't know what's going on.

302
00:18:59,998 --> 00:19:03,363
With you, I lose every single time.

303
00:19:04,158 --> 00:19:06,883
Come on, Wayu.

304
00:19:06,883 --> 00:19:08,885
You're making me blush so hard.

305
00:19:12,192 --> 00:19:15,232
Eek!

306
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:17,856
Eek!

307
00:19:18,048 --> 00:19:18,560
Phew.

308
00:19:19,602 --> 00:19:21,930
All clear. Nothing suspicious.

309
00:19:24,116 --> 00:19:26,061
Lick? Where are you
going to lick me then?

310
00:19:27,381 --> 00:19:28,928
I didn't say 'lick'.

311
00:19:28,928 --> 00:19:31,455
You really hear whatever you want, huh?

312
00:19:31,768 --> 00:19:34,408
My ears must be playing tricks on me.

313
00:19:34,408 --> 00:19:35,231
Listen.

314
00:19:35,231 --> 00:19:35,872
Hmm?

315
00:19:36,140 --> 00:19:41,094
I've got something even more fun
than playing games.

316
00:19:41,094 --> 00:19:42,812
In case you're interested.

317
00:19:44,302 --> 00:19:45,821
What is it?

318
00:19:46,218 --> 00:19:49,185
You should take me
somewhere else sometime.

319
00:19:49,483 --> 00:19:52,592
I feel kind of tense here.

320
00:19:52,919 --> 00:19:55,275
I want to have even more fun with you.

321
00:19:55,715 --> 00:19:58,512
What about you?

322
00:19:59,732 --> 00:20:00,925
Of course I do.

323
00:20:11,216 --> 00:20:12,544
Let me top that up for you.

324
00:20:12,544 --> 00:20:13,824
Okay.

325
00:20:21,248 --> 00:20:21,824
Ah.

326
00:20:34,298 --> 00:20:37,236
I think this spot is better.

327
00:20:37,728 --> 00:20:38,336
Oops.

328
00:20:39,323 --> 00:20:41,807
Wow, that's a lot, Wayu.

329
00:20:41,856 --> 00:20:42,944
It's really hard.

330
00:20:42,944 --> 00:20:44,128
That hard, huh?

331
00:20:44,128 --> 00:20:44,704
Yeah.

332
00:20:45,314 --> 00:20:47,358
I like it.

333
00:20:48,295 --> 00:20:50,282
Yes, yes, oh yes.

334
00:20:50,282 --> 00:20:51,872
Ah, I can't take it anymore.

335
00:20:51,872 --> 00:20:52,480
- Go ahead and lie down first.
- Whew.

336
00:20:56,145 --> 00:20:58,714
I love you, Wayu.

337
00:21:23,016 --> 00:21:24,251
This area's clear too.

338
00:21:43,103 --> 00:21:45,119
The party's started,
but Chain still isn't here.

339
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:14,191
The suspect's car just pulled
into the parking lot.

340
00:22:18,478 --> 00:22:19,301
Okay.

341
00:22:21,430 --> 00:22:23,020
If the suspect's already inside,

342
00:22:25,050 --> 00:22:26,668
wait for my signal only.

343
00:22:30,432 --> 00:22:32,204
(This area is clear)

344
00:22:33,879 --> 00:22:36,690
Wayu, I'm really drunk.

345
00:22:36,690 --> 00:22:38,947
Seriously, are you going to take me
all the way home?

346
00:22:38,947 --> 00:22:40,353
I can probably only
walk you to your car.

347
00:22:40,353 --> 00:22:41,133
- Seriously?
- Want to keep this going?

348
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:41,664
- We can head back later.
- Oh!

349
00:22:41,664 --> 00:22:43,248
Ow, ow.

350
00:22:43,248 --> 00:22:45,747
Hold on... I'll be back
to see you next time.

351
00:22:45,747 --> 00:22:47,280
Sure. Take it easy.

352
00:22:47,280 --> 00:22:48,032
I'll come see you again.

353
00:22:48,032 --> 00:22:48,941
- Easy there.
- Muah, muah.

354
00:22:49,707 --> 00:22:50,400
Sit down slowly.

355
00:23:02,199 --> 00:23:04,992
(Not important. Don't send it)

356
00:23:05,663 --> 00:23:07,423
Not important. Don't send it.

357
00:23:08,096 --> 00:23:08,743
Huh?

358
00:23:08,743 --> 00:23:10,802
How will I know what's important or not?

359
00:23:25,082 --> 00:23:25,962
Is it important?

360
00:23:27,325 --> 00:23:28,177
It is important.

361
00:24:10,266 --> 00:24:10,990
Darn it.

362
00:24:16,867 --> 00:24:17,860
Everybody, with me.

363
00:24:33,773 --> 00:24:35,065
There are cops here.

364
00:24:35,093 --> 00:24:36,272
They're heading upstairs.

365
00:25:06,607 --> 00:25:09,389
Darn it, they caught on.

366
00:25:10,184 --> 00:25:11,164
Sergeant, check the area.

367
00:25:11,164 --> 00:25:11,968
See if you can find anything.

368
00:25:12,064 --> 00:25:12,736
Yes, sir.

369
00:25:20,107 --> 00:25:23,145
Captain, there's still one suspect left.

370
00:25:28,212 --> 00:25:29,632
Looks like he's high.

371
00:25:30,924 --> 00:25:32,144
Your friends must really love you,

372
00:25:32,144 --> 00:25:33,365
leaving you behind like this.

373
00:25:34,827 --> 00:25:36,006
Take him to the station.

374
00:25:47,050 --> 00:25:49,207
I knew he looked familiar.

375
00:25:49,207 --> 00:25:50,570
So he's an actor.

376
00:25:52,231 --> 00:25:53,154
What is it, Sergeant?

377
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:55,127
Here you go.

378
00:26:07,647 --> 00:26:08,272
Excuse me.

379
00:26:08,272 --> 00:26:10,316
Could I see the full list of guests
staying here today?

380
00:26:10,813 --> 00:26:11,877
Sorry, sir.

381
00:26:11,877 --> 00:26:13,425
I can't show that to you.

382
00:26:15,296 --> 00:26:16,544
(Investigation)

383
00:26:18,265 --> 00:26:19,301
Just a moment, please.

384
00:26:22,325 --> 00:26:23,219
Here you go.

385
00:26:32,744 --> 00:26:34,490
Oh, you're still here?

386
00:26:35,257 --> 00:26:36,648
Yeah, I'm heading out soon.

387
00:26:37,642 --> 00:26:40,680
Ken, aren't you off today?
What are you doing here?

388
00:26:41,659 --> 00:26:43,859
There was a party,
and the cops raided it, bro.

389
00:26:44,224 --> 00:26:44,800
Oh.

390
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:47,437
What rotten luck.
And at a classy party, too.

391
00:26:47,607 --> 00:26:49,523
Good thing I got out.

392
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:50,496
That's good.

393
00:26:50,592 --> 00:26:53,484
One of my regulars happened
to text me at the right time.

394
00:26:53,484 --> 00:26:55,897
Since I was already dressed,
I just came straight here.

395
00:26:56,266 --> 00:26:57,813
Hey, who booked you?

396
00:26:59,077 --> 00:26:59,999
Nut did.

397
00:27:00,695 --> 00:27:01,618
You know him?

398
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:02,688
Hmph.

399
00:27:02,782 --> 00:27:05,252
He's some kind of producer.

400
00:27:05,252 --> 00:27:07,111
He likes taking boys
to high-society parties.

401
00:27:07,367 --> 00:27:08,673
The tips here are insane.

402
00:27:13,613 --> 00:27:14,763
Really, Ken?

403
00:27:15,657 --> 00:27:16,480
Yeah, seriously.

404
00:27:17,190 --> 00:27:18,595
What if...

405
00:27:18,595 --> 00:27:21,094
I wanted to take this kind of job.
What would I have to do?

406
00:27:21,792 --> 00:27:22,432
Hmm.

407
00:27:22,470 --> 00:27:25,466
You could try asking him.
He's kind of screening guys.

408
00:27:26,502 --> 00:27:30,605
I think you'll pass
Nut's screening, though.

409
00:27:30,917 --> 00:27:32,620
But Sky...

410
00:27:33,671 --> 00:27:34,466
Sky?

411
00:27:35,772 --> 00:27:37,362
What's Sky got to do with it?

412
00:27:38,015 --> 00:27:40,371
Well, Sky's Nut's main guy.

413
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:47,426
Oh, that Sky,
the one with tons of regulars.

414
00:27:47,710 --> 00:27:49,825
And every one of them is loaded.

415
00:27:49,825 --> 00:27:50,748
Seriously.

416
00:27:51,372 --> 00:27:54,368
Well, that Chain guy
you used to drink with?

417
00:27:54,368 --> 00:27:57,718
He's friends with Nut too.
I saw him at the party today.

418
00:27:58,726 --> 00:27:59,492
Really?

419
00:27:59,492 --> 00:28:01,266
Of course. Why would I lie?

420
00:28:03,580 --> 00:28:04,915
Thanks, man.

421
00:28:06,533 --> 00:28:07,441
No problem.

422
00:28:07,456 --> 00:28:08,421
Alright, I'm off then.

423
00:28:08,421 --> 00:28:09,798
- Okay, see you around.
- See you.

424
00:28:36,301 --> 00:28:37,237
Alright.

425
00:28:37,961 --> 00:28:39,069
Krit.

426
00:28:48,768 --> 00:28:49,312
Ouch!

427
00:28:49,312 --> 00:28:49,984
Krit.

428
00:28:49,984 --> 00:28:51,688
Ouch!

429
00:28:51,688 --> 00:28:52,696
Krit.

430
00:28:54,542 --> 00:28:55,606
Krit.

431
00:28:58,275 --> 00:29:00,461
I think you're punishing me,
not teaching me anymore.

432
00:29:01,057 --> 00:29:02,888
You're just getting back at me.

433
00:29:19,085 --> 00:29:21,016
Who told you to send that many messages?

434
00:29:21,016 --> 00:29:23,486
Didn't I tell you to send
only the important ones?

435
00:29:26,879 --> 00:29:29,164
How was I supposed to know
what's important and what's not?

436
00:29:29,476 --> 00:29:31,188
It's my first time working
as an informant.

437
00:29:31,336 --> 00:29:33,139
How am I supposed to know what to do?

438
00:29:48,157 --> 00:29:50,769
You'll find out today.
I'm going hard on you.

439
00:29:54,971 --> 00:29:55,993
We'll start with...

440
00:29:57,697 --> 00:29:58,719
Alright.

441
00:31:10,022 --> 00:31:11,825
The key skill in Jiu-Jitsu

442
00:31:11,995 --> 00:31:14,067
is to find the right moment to throw
when they're off guard.

443
00:31:21,832 --> 00:31:22,627
Whoa, Krit.

444
00:31:24,047 --> 00:31:26,148
My whole body aches.

445
00:31:31,968 --> 00:31:32,990
Help me out here.

446
00:32:10,551 --> 00:32:12,382
The key skill in Jiu-Jitsu...

447
00:32:13,361 --> 00:32:14,611
Is it something like this, Krit?

448
00:32:18,756 --> 00:32:19,934
You're a fast learner.

449
00:32:20,672 --> 00:32:22,049
I think you're ready for the field.

450
00:32:22,347 --> 00:32:23,539
Next comes the theory.

451
00:32:30,183 --> 00:32:31,205
What kind of theory?

452
00:32:32,582 --> 00:32:33,675
Detecting lies.

453
00:32:39,751 --> 00:32:41,440
The things you like to do.

454
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:43,683
Other than working as a bar host,
what else are you into?

455
00:32:46,266 --> 00:32:47,359
I like it?

456
00:32:51,575 --> 00:32:52,824
Maybe spending time with Singto.

457
00:32:53,875 --> 00:32:55,238
Even though I'm tired,

458
00:32:55,678 --> 00:32:57,225
I'm still happy.

459
00:33:02,875 --> 00:33:04,294
How many partners have you had?

460
00:33:07,105 --> 00:33:09,092
And what does that
have to do with anything?

461
00:33:11,704 --> 00:33:12,641
Just answer me.

462
00:33:20,165 --> 00:33:22,038
I've never had a partner.

463
00:33:30,598 --> 00:33:33,168
Do you have any particular
sexual preferences?

464
00:33:40,152 --> 00:33:40,918
Well...

465
00:33:42,068 --> 00:33:43,715
I've never

466
00:33:44,126 --> 00:33:45,447
been with anyone.

467
00:33:46,752 --> 00:33:49,691
So I don't really know
what my preferences are.

468
00:33:59,926 --> 00:34:00,820
Really?

469
00:34:05,277 --> 00:34:06,016
Hey...

470
00:34:07,094 --> 00:34:08,769
Do you really find what I said

471
00:34:09,053 --> 00:34:10,828
that hard to believe?

472
00:34:12,645 --> 00:34:13,539
Yeah, kind of.

473
00:34:17,414 --> 00:34:18,763
But you do seem sincere.

474
00:34:19,757 --> 00:34:20,949
Or if you are lying...

475
00:34:21,460 --> 00:34:23,036
Then you must be a really good liar.

476
00:34:35,017 --> 00:34:36,294
So what do you think?

477
00:34:45,762 --> 00:34:46,628
I might believe you.

478
00:34:49,212 --> 00:34:51,015
What's your type, then?

479
00:34:54,081 --> 00:34:55,969
My type?

480
00:35:00,512 --> 00:35:01,406
Well...

481
00:35:02,172 --> 00:35:03,166
Fair-skinned.

482
00:35:04,330 --> 00:35:05,267
East Asian.

483
00:35:07,013 --> 00:35:08,106
Beautiful eyes.

484
00:35:09,213 --> 00:35:10,505
Looks dignified.

485
00:35:11,910 --> 00:35:12,776
And then

486
00:35:13,642 --> 00:35:14,920
Seems like a leader.

487
00:35:18,341 --> 00:35:19,505
You're not talking about me, right?

488
00:35:27,923 --> 00:35:30,095
How could I mean you?

489
00:35:32,352 --> 00:35:32,992
Hmm.

490
00:35:37,348 --> 00:35:39,293
Look at those eyes.

491
00:35:40,003 --> 00:35:41,210
Big eyes like these.

492
00:35:42,530 --> 00:35:43,921
I wouldn't call that East Asian.

493
00:35:44,957 --> 00:35:46,533
And look at the skin.

494
00:35:46,873 --> 00:35:48,150
The skin tone is like this.

495
00:35:48,918 --> 00:35:49,556
Well...

496
00:35:49,897 --> 00:35:52,197
It's not the shade of white I prefer.

497
00:35:55,958 --> 00:35:57,364
Then why are you blushing?

498
00:36:01,821 --> 00:36:02,488
Well...

499
00:36:03,851 --> 00:36:05,980
It's hot in here, okay? Really hot.

500
00:36:11,204 --> 00:36:12,595
So hot your ears turned red too, huh?

501
00:36:14,767 --> 00:36:15,619
You...

502
00:36:16,158 --> 00:36:17,748
You need to learn to hide
your feelings better.

503
00:36:18,316 --> 00:36:19,551
You're so flustered,

504
00:36:19,679 --> 00:36:21,851
anyone could tell something's off.

505
00:36:23,852 --> 00:36:24,846
And remember this,

506
00:36:25,840 --> 00:36:27,359
little details like these...

507
00:36:28,366 --> 00:36:30,609
can become key evidence.

508
00:36:34,627 --> 00:36:36,657
Yes, Officer.

509
00:36:46,082 --> 00:36:46,863
Uh, Krit.

510
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:51,065
Did you look into that Producer Nut,
like I asked?

511
00:36:53,376 --> 00:36:53,952
Mm.

512
00:36:55,593 --> 00:36:56,587
Nut's name

513
00:36:56,913 --> 00:36:58,986
was on the guest list
we got from the hotel.

514
00:37:00,292 --> 00:37:01,768
So Nut and Chain really are friends.

515
00:37:02,236 --> 00:37:03,344
Looks like they're working together.

516
00:37:04,721 --> 00:37:05,927
But I still don't have any proof.

517
00:37:09,604 --> 00:37:10,654
In that case...

518
00:37:11,492 --> 00:37:14,473
If I can get into one of their parties,

519
00:37:15,594 --> 00:37:18,362
getting evidence shouldn't be
too hard, right?

520
00:37:20,989 --> 00:37:22,365
But from what I've heard,

521
00:37:23,089 --> 00:37:24,367
those parties of theirs

522
00:37:24,466 --> 00:37:25,914
are very selective.

523
00:37:27,007 --> 00:37:27,887
You up for this?

524
00:37:30,627 --> 00:37:31,223
Look.

525
00:37:32,089 --> 00:37:35,297
It's only my first day investigating,
and I already found you a lead.

526
00:37:35,681 --> 00:37:38,321
No positive vibes, and you're just
dumping negativity on me.

527
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:48,416
You...

528
00:37:49,493 --> 00:37:50,444
Honestly.

529
00:37:51,963 --> 00:37:53,184
I picked you

530
00:37:54,178 --> 00:37:55,598
because I believe in you.

531
00:37:59,813 --> 00:38:01,530
You've already done an amazing job.

532
00:38:14,817 --> 00:38:15,669
Thank you.

533
00:38:17,940 --> 00:38:19,104
Is there anything else?

534
00:38:19,970 --> 00:38:21,702
If not, I'll go change.

535
00:38:22,823 --> 00:38:24,158
I need to hurry and pick up Singto.

536
00:38:39,744 --> 00:38:40,610
Wait.

537
00:38:42,214 --> 00:38:43,705
- Yes?
- One more thing you need to know.

538
00:38:44,741 --> 00:38:45,621
What is it?

539
00:38:47,736 --> 00:38:49,326
Every conversation

540
00:38:49,752 --> 00:38:51,683
can be important evidence and clues

541
00:38:52,066 --> 00:38:53,883
that could lead to solving the case.

542
00:38:55,359 --> 00:38:57,006
And they're very hard to collect.

543
00:38:58,283 --> 00:38:59,178
So,

544
00:38:59,859 --> 00:39:00,980
you have to make it seamless.

545
00:39:03,252 --> 00:39:03,919
Yes.

546
00:39:04,543 --> 00:39:05,296
Then...

547
00:39:06,375 --> 00:39:08,206
How do I make it seamless?

548
00:39:16,384 --> 00:39:16,928
Hey!

549
00:39:17,603 --> 00:39:18,469
Hey, bro.

550
00:39:20,736 --> 00:39:21,351
Hey!

551
00:39:21,351 --> 00:39:22,685
Krit, wait.

552
00:39:22,884 --> 00:39:23,636
Krit.

553
00:39:30,308 --> 00:39:31,870
Since when were you hiding that?

554
00:39:32,778 --> 00:39:34,226
You didn't have that
when we were grappling.

555
00:39:34,936 --> 00:39:37,604
I told you it had to be seamless.

556
00:39:38,186 --> 00:39:39,677
Normally, when you're out investigating,

557
00:39:40,500 --> 00:39:42,104
you should always have some gear on you.

558
00:39:43,013 --> 00:39:44,574
You absolutely cannot get caught.

559
00:39:49,003 --> 00:39:50,763
And stop having such dirty thoughts.

560
00:39:53,702 --> 00:39:54,426
Hey.

561
00:39:54,951 --> 00:39:56,882
You just reached in there like that.

562
00:39:56,910 --> 00:39:58,202
Anyone would think that.

563
00:39:58,315 --> 00:39:59,125
Anyway.

564
00:39:59,749 --> 00:40:01,084
Wait here for a bit.

565
00:40:01,793 --> 00:40:03,057
Once you're changed,

566
00:40:03,497 --> 00:40:04,377
I'll take you.

567
00:40:04,959 --> 00:40:05,854
Oh, it's okay.

568
00:40:05,854 --> 00:40:06,905
I can go back on my own.

569
00:40:13,320 --> 00:40:14,498
So stubborn.

570
00:40:21,099 --> 00:40:23,399
A, your mom's here.

571
00:40:27,089 --> 00:40:28,928
Go on, your mom's over there.

572
00:40:28,928 --> 00:40:29,664
Go.

573
00:40:29,900 --> 00:40:31,392
Let's go to your mom

574
00:40:31,904 --> 00:40:32,736
Dad's not home yet.

575
00:40:33,179 --> 00:40:34,542
Yes.

576
00:40:37,952 --> 00:40:38,496
Here you go.

577
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:40,480
Oh.

578
00:40:41,739 --> 00:40:42,676
Thank you.

579
00:40:54,713 --> 00:40:56,161
Yes.

580
00:40:58,518 --> 00:41:00,094
Do you have any plans for the future?

581
00:41:00,945 --> 00:41:02,223
Do you plan on going back to study?

582
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:04,096
Wow.

583
00:41:04,906 --> 00:41:05,941
Honestly,

584
00:41:06,155 --> 00:41:08,937
I haven't really planned that far ahead.

585
00:41:10,016 --> 00:41:12,514
Right now, just making enough to
support Singto is already hard enough.

586
00:41:14,260 --> 00:41:14,928
But...

587
00:41:15,822 --> 00:41:16,872
You never know.

588
00:41:17,284 --> 00:41:19,924
Maybe one day, if I make enough money,

589
00:41:20,407 --> 00:41:22,834
I might go back and finish my studies.

590
00:41:26,426 --> 00:41:28,059
And when you say "enough",

591
00:41:28,300 --> 00:41:30,330
how much do you mean?

592
00:41:33,126 --> 00:41:34,347
I don't really know.

593
00:41:36,306 --> 00:41:37,356
Actually, I think...

594
00:41:38,009 --> 00:41:39,713
it might never be enough.

595
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:47,037
But the time I'm happiest

596
00:41:47,662 --> 00:41:49,110
is when I'm studying.

597
00:41:52,929 --> 00:41:53,823
What about you?

598
00:41:54,547 --> 00:41:55,753
Why did you become a cop?

599
00:42:03,390 --> 00:42:04,796
My dad was a cop.

600
00:42:05,236 --> 00:42:06,655
He wanted me to become one too.

601
00:42:09,248 --> 00:42:09,920
Well!

602
00:42:10,162 --> 00:42:12,149
But that's your dad's dream.

603
00:42:13,611 --> 00:42:15,187
What about your dream?

604
00:42:16,209 --> 00:42:16,975
What do you want to do?

605
00:42:16,975 --> 00:42:17,969
It's pointless to know.

606
00:42:18,821 --> 00:42:20,595
In the end, I still have to be a cop.

607
00:42:25,436 --> 00:42:29,368
Wow, being a cop is so cool.

608
00:42:29,623 --> 00:42:32,306
Look, they even have
an arch of sabers at the wedding.

609
00:42:32,732 --> 00:42:35,231
Ms. Rose is so lucky.

610
00:42:38,808 --> 00:42:40,298
Why do you say Rose is lucky?

611
00:42:41,505 --> 00:42:42,044
Huh?

612
00:42:42,924 --> 00:42:44,812
Because you and Ms. Rose are dating.

613
00:42:45,366 --> 00:42:48,077
You're lucky too, having Ms. Rose
as your girlfriend.

614
00:42:48,588 --> 00:42:50,491
She's beautiful and talented.

615
00:42:50,604 --> 00:42:51,868
If it were me,

616
00:42:51,882 --> 00:42:53,883
I'd drop to one knee
and propose right away.

617
00:42:54,210 --> 00:42:55,473
Before she slipped through my fingers.

618
00:42:57,205 --> 00:42:59,008
Who told you I was dating Rose?

619
00:43:00,300 --> 00:43:01,009
Oh, come on.

620
00:43:01,804 --> 00:43:04,657
Everyone knows.
I have a phone, you know.

621
00:43:07,325 --> 00:43:08,187
I'm single.

622
00:43:09,342 --> 00:43:11,500
Rose and I have been friends
since college.

623
00:43:14,963 --> 00:43:16,340
You still don't have a partner?

624
00:43:18,725 --> 00:43:19,463
No.

625
00:43:22,189 --> 00:43:23,509
Why are you so surprised?

626
00:43:28,222 --> 00:43:29,670
Hello, Father.

627
00:43:29,670 --> 00:43:31,728
- Hello.
- Singto is here.

628
00:43:31,813 --> 00:43:33,077
Singto.

629
00:43:33,815 --> 00:43:34,922
How are you? Having fun?

630
00:43:34,922 --> 00:43:36,058
Are you having fun? Tired?

631
00:43:37,179 --> 00:43:38,201
I bought this for you.

632
00:43:39,166 --> 00:43:40,089
Eat slowly, okay?

633
00:43:41,225 --> 00:43:42,417
Say thank you.

634
00:43:44,774 --> 00:43:45,654
Is it good?

635
00:43:48,649 --> 00:43:49,515
You're eating so fast.

636
00:43:55,488 --> 00:43:56,096
Sigh.

637
00:44:02,475 --> 00:44:04,150
Seeing you this happy...

638
00:44:04,661 --> 00:44:07,287
So, have you made your move
on that taken guy yet?

639
00:44:07,642 --> 00:44:09,715
Tai, keep it down. Darn it.

640
00:44:09,824 --> 00:44:10,848
Hey, hey, hey.

641
00:44:11,559 --> 00:44:13,192
What do you mean, "make a move on" him?

642
00:44:13,760 --> 00:44:15,904
Tai's just joking. It's nothing.

643
00:44:16,855 --> 00:44:18,786
Yeah, yeah. If it's nothing,

644
00:44:18,786 --> 00:44:20,716
then get dressed and get outside.

645
00:44:20,886 --> 00:44:21,894
Okay.

646
00:44:25,699 --> 00:44:26,778
The customers are waiting.

647
00:44:30,240 --> 00:44:31,392
(New Post)

648
00:44:35,168 --> 00:44:38,437
(Ready for love... No! Ready for battle,
no matter how many hits it takes)

649
00:44:39,752 --> 00:44:43,155
You know there's
a Close Friends list, right?

650
00:44:43,329 --> 00:44:45,019
Darn, you scared me.

651
00:44:45,899 --> 00:44:48,383
You don't need to make
a whole new IG account.

652
00:44:48,553 --> 00:44:52,329
Come on! Stories only
stay up for 24 hours.

653
00:44:53,039 --> 00:44:54,899
- I just don't want it to disappear.
- Oh wow.

654
00:44:56,304 --> 00:44:57,581
Oh, how romantic.

655
00:44:58,220 --> 00:45:00,023
And you're not even together yet.

656
00:45:00,165 --> 00:45:03,359
If you were dating, wouldn't you build
a world just for the two of you?

657
00:45:03,359 --> 00:45:04,097
- Hmm?
- Huh?

658
00:45:04,424 --> 00:45:05,659
I can do that?

659
00:45:05,942 --> 00:45:07,192
If I could,

660
00:45:07,192 --> 00:45:08,739
I would've done it already.

661
00:45:28,286 --> 00:45:31,494
Sorry, I'm a little busy today.
Thought you might bail.

662
00:45:32,374 --> 00:45:34,602
We made plans, so of course I came.

663
00:45:34,844 --> 00:45:38,720
Oh, please. The other day,
you ditched me just to tutor Wayu.

664
00:45:39,713 --> 00:45:41,289
That was only once.

665
00:45:44,625 --> 00:45:45,689
Since we're on the subject...

666
00:45:47,066 --> 00:45:49,380
why don't you seriously pursue Wayu?

667
00:45:51,722 --> 00:45:54,349
What do you mean? I was working.

668
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:57,188
Sure. I'll wait and see.

669
00:45:57,188 --> 00:45:59,954
Just don't show up next time
already dating him.

670
00:46:00,637 --> 00:46:01,773
You're talking nonsense.

671
00:46:02,724 --> 00:46:03,732
No way.

672
00:46:03,840 --> 00:46:04,864
Hm?

673
00:46:30,107 --> 00:46:32,463
Oh! Sky, Nut's here too.

674
00:46:36,778 --> 00:46:39,121
Oh, Nut! Hello there.

675
00:46:39,376 --> 00:46:41,946
Long time no see. I missed you.

676
00:46:41,946 --> 00:46:44,203
Missed you too. But I'm here every day.

677
00:46:44,203 --> 00:46:45,409
I'm the one who invited him.

678
00:46:46,545 --> 00:46:47,979
See?

679
00:46:48,546 --> 00:46:51,329
Foei brought him to the table
on the right side of the stage.

680
00:46:52,245 --> 00:46:53,381
Same as usual.

681
00:46:54,040 --> 00:46:56,240
You'd definitely pass Nut's standards.

682
00:46:56,240 --> 00:46:57,773
But Sky...

683
00:46:57,972 --> 00:46:59,463
What's Sky got to do with it?

684
00:46:59,463 --> 00:47:01,081
Sky's Nut's main guy.

685
00:47:05,794 --> 00:47:06,546
Let's go.

686
00:51:26,377 --> 00:51:30,863
Alright, the show's over.
That was seriously hot.

687
00:51:30,863 --> 00:51:32,608
- Did you like it?
- Loved it!

688
00:51:32,608 --> 00:51:34,426
You did.

689
00:51:34,426 --> 00:51:35,391
If you did,

690
00:51:35,391 --> 00:51:40,246
let's give Moonlit a big round
of applause one more time!

691
00:51:40,573 --> 00:51:43,667
And since today is Valentine's Day,

692
00:51:43,667 --> 00:51:49,258
we're giving heart stickers
to all our customers.

693
00:51:49,729 --> 00:51:53,150
If you want to give
your heart to someone,

694
00:51:53,150 --> 00:51:56,401
you can stick a sticker
on one of the boys.

695
00:51:57,919 --> 00:52:01,965
Each sticker counts as one drink.

696
00:52:02,987 --> 00:52:06,240
Go ahead and pick your favorite.

697
00:52:08,544 --> 00:52:09,760
Hey.

698
00:52:13,568 --> 00:52:15,507
Ow!

699
00:52:15,507 --> 00:52:17,339
Nut, you...

700
00:52:17,580 --> 00:52:19,993
- Wayu.
- Hello there.

701
00:52:19,993 --> 00:52:21,839
- Hi.
- Nut...

702
00:52:22,378 --> 00:52:26,367
When did you get here?
How come I didn't see you?

703
00:52:26,949 --> 00:52:29,419
I've been here a while,
at the usual table.

704
00:52:30,640 --> 00:52:32,144
You just weren't paying attention to me.

705
00:52:33,748 --> 00:52:34,558
Well...

706
00:52:35,353 --> 00:52:38,845
Then stop looking at other people
so much. I noticed, you know.

707
00:52:39,360 --> 00:52:39,968
Right here.

708
00:52:40,662 --> 00:52:42,507
Come here. I'll cut out
a sticker for you.

709
00:52:43,600 --> 00:52:44,352
Where should I put it?

710
00:52:44,751 --> 00:52:46,908
Right here. Can you put it
right over my heart?

711
00:52:47,163 --> 00:52:49,974
- Love you, Wayu.
- Sky.

712
00:52:49,974 --> 00:52:52,330
- Sky.
- Uh, Nut.

713
00:52:52,352 --> 00:52:52,997
Umm.

714
00:52:52,997 --> 00:52:55,169
You danced really well.

715
00:52:55,456 --> 00:52:56,960
- Hello!
- You're a great dancer.

716
00:52:56,960 --> 00:52:59,657
- This is for the talented one.
- Thank you.

717
00:53:01,184 --> 00:53:03,168
I've got one left. Can I put it here?

718
00:53:03,552 --> 00:53:04,352
Right here, okay?

719
00:53:04,832 --> 00:53:05,472
Put it on straight.

720
00:53:12,192 --> 00:53:13,120
Want another?

721
00:53:13,856 --> 00:53:14,400
Pin it.

722
00:53:25,024 --> 00:53:25,536
Huh?

723
00:53:27,264 --> 00:53:28,096
This is fantastic.

724
00:53:28,301 --> 00:53:30,104
What on earth is Wayu doing?

725
00:53:30,572 --> 00:53:32,546
Sky's going to tear him apart again.

726
00:53:33,000 --> 00:53:35,342
I think he's trying to boost his stats.

727
00:53:36,449 --> 00:53:37,571
By doing this?

728
00:53:38,224 --> 00:53:39,643
This is definitely going to
end in a fight.

729
00:53:42,894 --> 00:53:43,717
Thank you.

730
00:53:45,984 --> 00:53:46,720
Joam.

731
00:53:46,848 --> 00:53:47,552
Cute, right?

732
00:53:49,395 --> 00:53:50,261
See you later, Nut.

733
00:54:11,904 --> 00:54:12,736
Awesome job. Awesome.

734
00:54:14,479 --> 00:54:16,579
Hey, hold up, Wayu.

735
00:54:16,622 --> 00:54:19,802
You're lucky, someone booked you
for a hundred drinks today.

736
00:54:19,930 --> 00:54:20,881
Is that true?

737
00:54:20,881 --> 00:54:21,661
Yeah, it's true.

738
00:54:22,598 --> 00:54:23,961
Come on, I'll take you to the table.

739
00:54:26,272 --> 00:54:28,096
- I'm right up front.
- I called you...

740
00:54:28,163 --> 00:54:31,144
Hey, Wayu. This table.

741
00:54:33,458 --> 00:54:34,153
Hurry up.

742
00:54:37,078 --> 00:54:38,753
I've been here with you the whole time.

743
00:54:38,824 --> 00:54:40,172
Here he is. Wayu.

744
00:54:41,819 --> 00:54:43,593
Hello, hello, hello.

745
00:54:43,593 --> 00:54:45,581
Hello, I'm Mind.

746
00:54:46,021 --> 00:54:47,980
These are my friends, Heng and Net.

747
00:54:48,093 --> 00:54:49,782
Nice to meet you. I'm Wayu.

748
00:54:50,364 --> 00:54:52,437
Where would you like me to sit?

749
00:54:52,948 --> 00:54:54,992
You can sit next to Mind.
Mind requested you.

750
00:54:56,383 --> 00:54:57,121
Sure.

751
00:54:58,839 --> 00:55:01,905
Please take good care of Wayu for me.

752
00:55:01,905 --> 00:55:03,381
Okay, take good care of them.

753
00:55:05,269 --> 00:55:06,845
I'll take care of you tonight.

754
00:55:08,392 --> 00:55:09,017
Come on.

755
00:55:10,862 --> 00:55:12,623
Come on, come on. If you want a sticker,

756
00:55:12,623 --> 00:55:13,588
I'll put it on for you.

757
00:55:13,588 --> 00:55:14,397
Really, Nut?

758
00:55:14,397 --> 00:55:15,675
Hmm, I'll put one on everyone.

759
00:55:15,712 --> 00:55:17,152
Oops, wow.

760
00:55:17,492 --> 00:55:18,500
How many do you want?

761
00:55:18,500 --> 00:55:20,302
A hundred, if you can handle that.

762
00:55:21,594 --> 00:55:23,099
You've gotten plenty from me already.

763
00:55:23,099 --> 00:55:23,712
Whoa.

764
00:55:23,712 --> 00:55:25,626
That's not much. Keep going.

765
00:55:25,626 --> 00:55:26,534
Come here. I'll put some on you.

766
00:55:26,534 --> 00:55:27,372
Whoa.

767
00:55:27,372 --> 00:55:28,280
Thank you.

768
00:55:28,280 --> 00:55:30,367
Wow, Nut, isn't this a bit much?

769
00:55:30,821 --> 00:55:33,021
I can give you more.
Where do you want it?

770
00:55:33,263 --> 00:55:33,972
Nut.

771
00:55:33,972 --> 00:55:35,946
I'll just go to the restroom
for a moment.

772
00:55:36,201 --> 00:55:37,550
- Hurry back.
- Okay.

773
00:55:37,550 --> 00:55:38,816
Don't show it like this.

774
00:55:40,957 --> 00:55:41,751
Come on.

775
00:55:42,272 --> 00:55:42,816
- Come on.
- That one's better.

776
00:55:50,269 --> 00:55:52,497
So, have you worked here long?

777
00:55:52,795 --> 00:55:54,612
Yeah, for a while now.

778
00:55:55,407 --> 00:55:58,928
If I'd known you were here,
I'd have come over ages ago.

779
00:56:00,248 --> 00:56:01,384
Thank you.

780
00:56:02,193 --> 00:56:04,606
By the way, Mind, I haven't asked you,

781
00:56:04,606 --> 00:56:06,650
how would you like me
to take care of you tonight?

782
00:56:07,289 --> 00:56:08,041
Like...

783
00:56:09,191 --> 00:56:10,156
Can we go for a boyfriend vibe?

784
00:56:12,924 --> 00:56:13,847
Of course.

785
00:56:15,991 --> 00:56:16,899
Absolutely.

786
00:56:18,205 --> 00:56:19,369
But actually,

787
00:56:20,292 --> 00:56:21,555
we're the same age.

788
00:56:22,961 --> 00:56:23,968
Really?

789
00:56:25,260 --> 00:56:27,943
Hmm. I might even be older.

790
00:56:28,397 --> 00:56:31,151
Same age. I've met you
at the university.

791
00:56:32,187 --> 00:56:33,152
Is that true?

792
00:56:33,184 --> 00:56:33,792
Mm-hmm.

793
00:56:35,339 --> 00:56:36,375
It's a small world, huh?

794
00:56:40,676 --> 00:56:41,656
But today,

795
00:56:42,919 --> 00:56:44,239
we're a couple.

796
00:56:50,414 --> 00:56:52,231
If there's anything you want
me to do, just say the word.

797
00:56:54,545 --> 00:56:55,326
Mm.

798
00:57:05,831 --> 00:57:09,152
You've poured me a lot.
You're only having a little.

799
00:57:10,430 --> 00:57:12,631
Mind, give me a second, okay?

800
00:57:12,631 --> 00:57:13,340
I'll be back soon.

801
00:57:13,609 --> 00:57:14,112
Okay, okay.

802
00:57:14,112 --> 00:57:14,720
Okay.

803
00:57:17,216 --> 00:57:18,688
Top it up.

804
00:57:19,273 --> 00:57:22,155
Go ahead. Go all out.

805
00:57:23,603 --> 00:57:24,412
Hi!

806
00:57:25,435 --> 00:57:26,812
This table looks a little lonely.

807
00:57:27,294 --> 00:57:29,806
Would you like to join us
for a round or two?

808
00:57:31,595 --> 00:57:34,136
Maybe we should wait for Sky
to get back first.

809
00:57:34,688 --> 00:57:35,296
Hey.

810
00:57:35,527 --> 00:57:37,500
It's just a couple of casual rounds.

811
00:57:39,615 --> 00:57:40,495
Sure.

812
00:57:42,781 --> 00:57:43,547
Hey there.

813
00:57:44,158 --> 00:57:45,166
Ferris wheel.

814
00:57:56,672 --> 00:57:57,248
Hey.

815
00:57:57,814 --> 00:57:59,049
How'd you end up sitting here?

816
00:57:59,168 --> 00:57:59,840
Well!

817
00:58:00,156 --> 00:58:03,165
A crowd like this is more fun,
isn't it, Sky?

818
00:58:09,184 --> 00:58:11,157
Get out. This is my spot.

819
00:58:15,274 --> 00:58:15,955
Uh...

820
00:58:20,455 --> 00:58:21,406
Oh, Nut.

821
00:58:21,747 --> 00:58:24,544
I was only gone for a second,
and there you go again.

822
00:58:24,586 --> 00:58:26,368
I haven't even done anything yet.

823
00:58:26,368 --> 00:58:27,908
Come on, Nut.

824
00:58:28,845 --> 00:58:29,682
Everyone,

825
00:58:29,924 --> 00:58:30,974
how about this?

826
00:58:31,215 --> 00:58:33,714
Why don't we play "Never Have I Ever"?

827
00:58:33,714 --> 00:58:35,233
It'll help us get to know
each other better.

828
00:58:35,673 --> 00:58:36,241
Sure.

829
00:58:36,496 --> 00:58:37,816
So, how do you play?

830
00:58:38,015 --> 00:58:39,889
I think I've played once, but I forgot.

831
00:58:40,528 --> 00:58:41,890
Wait, wait. I think...

832
00:58:42,132 --> 00:58:43,537
with this many people,

833
00:58:43,778 --> 00:58:46,561
King's Cup would be way more fun.

834
00:58:46,592 --> 00:58:47,232
Mm.

835
00:58:48,179 --> 00:58:49,002
Right, Nut?

836
00:58:49,471 --> 00:58:50,592
Come on, let's play King's Cup.

837
00:58:50,592 --> 00:58:52,295
Yeah, come on.

838
00:58:52,295 --> 00:58:53,147
I'll go first.

839
00:58:53,360 --> 00:58:54,269
First up.

840
00:58:56,672 --> 00:58:57,728
Three of clubs.

841
00:58:57,728 --> 00:58:58,688
One shot.

842
00:58:58,688 --> 00:59:02,885
One shot! One shot!

843
00:59:05,298 --> 00:59:07,030
Me! Me! Me!

844
00:59:07,783 --> 00:59:09,117
Here you go.

845
00:59:09,600 --> 00:59:11,516
- King.
- The King card, Nut got the King.

846
00:59:13,234 --> 00:59:14,383
Hold on.

847
00:59:14,383 --> 00:59:18,174
I order all the host boys
to take off their shirts.

848
00:59:20,289 --> 00:59:21,978
Will you take them off or not?

849
00:59:22,240 --> 00:59:23,136
Whoa.

850
00:59:23,354 --> 00:59:24,263
Get up.

851
00:59:24,263 --> 00:59:30,779
Take it off!

852
00:59:33,348 --> 00:59:35,194
Come on!

853
00:59:39,136 --> 00:59:41,152
Right here.

854
00:59:41,454 --> 00:59:42,533
Thank you.

855
00:59:42,533 --> 00:59:43,808
Can I have one too?

856
00:59:43,808 --> 00:59:44,790
Come here.

857
00:59:45,408 --> 00:59:46,272
It should be like this.

858
00:59:48,160 --> 00:59:49,048
Come here.

859
00:59:49,048 --> 00:59:51,660
Got it, thank you, Nut.

860
00:59:51,660 --> 00:59:53,184
Keep going!

861
00:59:53,184 --> 00:59:54,698
Come on!

862
00:59:54,698 --> 00:59:55,309
Next up...

863
00:59:56,160 --> 00:59:57,509
- Hey.
- Another king.

864
00:59:57,509 --> 00:59:58,204
King.

865
00:59:59,360 --> 01:00:01,440
Hey, wow.

866
01:00:02,321 --> 01:00:03,627
What should we do?

867
01:00:05,316 --> 01:00:07,971
Then I order...

868
01:00:12,911 --> 01:00:13,947
Wayu.

869
01:00:19,568 --> 01:00:21,314
Bow at my feet.

870
01:00:24,863 --> 01:00:25,942
How about that?

871
01:00:27,248 --> 01:00:28,100
How about that?

872
01:00:29,051 --> 01:00:30,854
Do it, so we can keep playing.

873
01:00:34,175 --> 01:00:40,520
Bow down!

874
01:00:41,784 --> 01:00:43,076
Hurry up!

875
01:00:43,648 --> 01:00:44,288
There.

876
01:00:53,888 --> 01:00:54,528
Hey!

877
01:00:55,965 --> 01:00:56,632
Sorry.

878
01:00:57,285 --> 01:00:58,747
Today, Wayu is my boyfriend.

879
01:00:59,443 --> 01:01:00,990
I really can't let my boyfriend
bow to anyone.

880
01:01:02,609 --> 01:01:05,206
In that case, let me down
this drink for him.

881
01:01:07,435 --> 01:01:08,216
Mind.

882
01:01:09,649 --> 01:01:10,359
Mind.

883
01:01:23,546 --> 01:01:24,398
Anyway...

884
01:01:24,952 --> 01:01:26,712
I'll take my boyfriend and friends
back to the table first.

885
01:01:30,304 --> 01:01:30,880
What a hero.

886
01:01:32,220 --> 01:01:33,256
- Let's head back.
- Man, you're such a hero.

887
01:01:33,280 --> 01:01:33,792
Really.

888
01:01:36,384 --> 01:01:37,184
Whoa.

889
01:01:37,217 --> 01:01:39,417
Nut, it's okay, right?

890
01:01:40,013 --> 01:01:41,234
That killed the mood.

891
01:01:41,589 --> 01:01:43,051
And we finally got the king card too.

892
01:01:43,207 --> 01:01:46,302
- Oh, what a waste, right, Nut?
- Sit, sit, sit.

893
01:01:46,302 --> 01:01:47,707
Sit, sit, sit.

894
01:01:49,056 --> 01:01:51,497
Mind, you really didn't
have to go that far.

895
01:01:51,497 --> 01:01:53,300
It's fine. It was nothing.

896
01:01:54,436 --> 01:01:55,103
Thank you.

897
01:01:57,743 --> 01:01:58,609
Thank you.

898
01:01:58,978 --> 01:02:00,398
Come on, let's go.

899
01:02:03,876 --> 01:02:04,798
I'll be right back.

900
01:02:06,336 --> 01:02:07,264
Where are you going?

901
01:02:07,264 --> 01:02:08,404
Just going to the restroom.

902
01:02:08,404 --> 01:02:09,248
Oh.

903
01:02:09,454 --> 01:02:10,176
Wait a sec.

904
01:02:10,272 --> 01:02:10,784
Okay.

905
01:02:28,377 --> 01:02:29,129
Oh, hey.

906
01:02:29,612 --> 01:02:32,011
Has anyone told you
Nut's car got sideswiped?

907
01:02:32,323 --> 01:02:33,516
What? Really?

908
01:02:34,339 --> 01:02:35,489
No one's told me anything.

909
01:02:36,085 --> 01:02:36,880
Oh, really?

910
01:02:38,498 --> 01:02:39,407
I think...

911
01:02:39,577 --> 01:02:41,678
You probably just
kept missing each other.

912
01:02:41,678 --> 01:02:44,077
Then maybe you should go
check on it first.

913
01:02:44,077 --> 01:02:45,794
Or, this could turn into a big problem.

914
01:02:45,794 --> 01:02:46,560
Go on, then.

915
01:02:47,824 --> 01:02:49,499
Stay here. I'll go check it out myself.

916
01:02:55,632 --> 01:02:56,342
Wayu.

917
01:02:56,416 --> 01:02:56,960
Oh.

918
01:02:59,010 --> 01:02:59,791
I know.

919
01:03:00,302 --> 01:03:01,523
I know what you're up to.

920
01:03:02,602 --> 01:03:04,348
Trying to cut in like this...

921
01:03:04,830 --> 01:03:06,534
Sky's not going to let that happen.

922
01:03:12,794 --> 01:03:13,617
Bro.

923
01:03:14,710 --> 01:03:16,953
I really want Nut as a regular client.

924
01:03:17,975 --> 01:03:18,799
Please, bro.

925
01:03:19,480 --> 01:03:20,914
How about this, will you help me?

926
01:03:22,163 --> 01:03:23,568
If you help me out

927
01:03:24,306 --> 01:03:26,847
whenever Nut comes in,
how much do I get?

928
01:03:27,415 --> 01:03:28,281
You can have it.

929
01:03:29,545 --> 01:03:30,822
15%.

930
01:03:34,314 --> 01:03:35,081
20.

931
01:03:43,939 --> 01:03:45,443
Fine. 20%, then.

932
01:03:46,948 --> 01:03:47,729
In that case...

933
01:03:48,084 --> 01:03:49,688
Keep a lookout for me, okay?

934
01:03:50,057 --> 01:03:51,561
I need some time to lure the target.

935
01:03:52,938 --> 01:03:55,039
- Thanks, bro.
- 20%, okay?

936
01:03:55,039 --> 01:03:56,019
20%.

937
01:04:13,920 --> 01:04:14,528
Oops.

938
01:04:14,841 --> 01:04:15,991
Be careful, okay?

939
01:04:18,958 --> 01:04:20,293
You've got game.

940
01:04:22,663 --> 01:04:23,714
With skills like that...

941
01:04:24,835 --> 01:04:26,567
want someone like me by your side?

942
01:04:27,646 --> 01:04:28,867
I'm still available.

943
01:04:33,665 --> 01:04:35,567
So, Nut...

944
01:04:36,660 --> 01:04:39,655
I heard from the others they went
to one of your parties,

945
01:04:39,982 --> 01:04:42,849
and you tip really well.

946
01:04:44,226 --> 01:04:46,171
If I wanted in on that kind of work,

947
01:04:47,250 --> 01:04:48,570
what would I have to do?

948
01:04:48,911 --> 01:04:50,511
Whether the work is hard or easy,

949
01:04:50,511 --> 01:04:52,715
whatever it is, I can handle anything.

950
01:04:52,928 --> 01:04:54,560
Just let me go there.

951
01:05:13,980 --> 01:05:14,774
Be careful.

952
01:05:16,166 --> 01:05:19,175
Hey, get a bottle and put it on my tab.

953
01:05:21,986 --> 01:05:22,766
And a glass too, please.

954
01:05:22,766 --> 01:05:23,456
Hey.

955
01:05:23,817 --> 01:05:25,208
A glass for what? No need.

956
01:05:32,419 --> 01:05:38,438
1, 2, 3, 4, 5,

957
01:05:38,523 --> 01:05:43,449
6, 7, 8, 9, 10.

958
01:05:49,255 --> 01:05:50,163
You okay?

959
01:05:50,944 --> 01:05:51,995
I'm okay.

960
01:05:56,622 --> 01:05:57,687
How's it going?

961
01:05:58,127 --> 01:06:00,143
Can I go to your house party now?

962
01:06:02,144 --> 01:06:03,791
Isn't that a bit too easy?

963
01:06:06,545 --> 01:06:07,496
But if...

964
01:06:10,449 --> 01:06:11,485
Join me for a hit,

965
01:06:13,103 --> 01:06:14,480
maybe I can bring you along.

966
01:06:16,595 --> 01:06:18,327
With looks like yours...

967
01:06:19,620 --> 01:06:21,536
I could even make you a star.

968
01:06:26,362 --> 01:06:27,838
Wow, Nut!

969
01:06:29,854 --> 01:06:32,522
I'd rather work your party, though.

970
01:06:33,417 --> 01:06:36,398
And I'm not even taking care
of your table tonight.

971
01:06:37,988 --> 01:06:41,607
I don't think that'd look very good.

972
01:06:46,278 --> 01:06:47,385
What a shame.

973
01:06:56,314 --> 01:06:57,393
Hold on.

974
01:06:58,968 --> 01:07:00,501
There's a party next week.

975
01:07:05,441 --> 01:07:06,449
Give me your Line.

976
01:07:07,045 --> 01:07:08,238
I'll send you the pin.

977
01:07:26,181 --> 01:07:27,103
Done.

978
01:07:28,523 --> 01:07:29,829
Thank you so much.

979
01:07:30,212 --> 01:07:33,675
I'll do everything I can.

980
01:07:36,586 --> 01:07:37,651
Give it your all.

981
01:07:37,651 --> 01:07:39,354
Yes, Nut.

982
01:08:01,257 --> 01:08:03,926
(Nut personally picks the host boys)

983
01:08:03,926 --> 01:08:07,815
(There'll probably be
drugs at the party)

984
01:08:07,815 --> 01:08:10,144
(Nut's throwing
another party next week)

985
01:08:29,634 --> 01:08:32,146
(I've gathered enough evidence
to bring Nut in.)

986
01:08:32,303 --> 01:08:33,907
(It's all thanks to you, Wayu.)

987
01:08:36,220 --> 01:08:37,030
How much?

988
01:08:37,654 --> 01:08:38,889
Just five thousand.

989
01:08:38,912 --> 01:08:39,940
Hmm.

990
01:08:39,940 --> 01:08:41,558
Then don't worry.

991
01:08:41,856 --> 01:08:44,766
It's not much. I'll find the money.

992
01:08:45,568 --> 01:08:46,342
It's not a problem.

993
01:08:46,342 --> 01:08:47,903
Thanks.

994
01:08:48,145 --> 01:08:49,238
Where will you get the money, Mom?

995
01:08:50,430 --> 01:08:51,566
Oh, Wayu.

996
01:08:55,129 --> 01:08:57,343
I thought you weren't coming
home tonight.

997
01:08:57,783 --> 01:08:59,047
Is this your son?

998
01:09:00,622 --> 01:09:01,744
Hi.

999
01:09:03,234 --> 01:09:05,349
From now on, we're going
to be one family.

1000
01:09:05,477 --> 01:09:06,783
What the hell are you talking about?

1001
01:09:07,876 --> 01:09:09,139
Calm down.

1002
01:09:09,154 --> 01:09:09,821
Mom.

1003
01:09:09,977 --> 01:09:11,368
In case you forgot...

1004
01:09:11,382 --> 01:09:13,866
Every baht you've been spending
is my money.

1005
01:09:14,037 --> 01:09:16,322
You've never helped earn it,
and I never said a word.

1006
01:09:16,379 --> 01:09:18,324
I can support you
and your grandchild just fine.

1007
01:09:18,324 --> 01:09:20,411
But I won't support some man
leeching off you.

1008
01:09:20,411 --> 01:09:21,376
That, I really can't do.

1009
01:09:21,376 --> 01:09:22,980
Can you watch your tone, Wayu?

1010
01:09:23,420 --> 01:09:25,504
Watch your tone, please.

1011
01:09:27,136 --> 01:09:27,808
Watch your tone, son.

1012
01:09:27,808 --> 01:09:28,530
Get out.

1013
01:09:29,396 --> 01:09:30,149
Wayu.

1014
01:09:31,227 --> 01:09:32,292
Wayu, watch your tone.

1015
01:09:32,292 --> 01:09:33,059
I said get out.

1016
01:09:33,073 --> 01:09:35,089
What's all this fuss about?

1017
01:09:35,089 --> 01:09:35,742
Whoa!

1018
01:09:35,742 --> 01:09:38,155
I'm your mother. This is my house too.

1019
01:09:38,751 --> 01:09:40,128
That's exactly because you're my mom.

1020
01:09:40,142 --> 01:09:42,172
Then why don't you act like one?

1021
01:09:42,172 --> 01:09:44,088
Stop bringing trouble home, Mom.

1022
01:09:44,128 --> 01:09:44,736
Wayu.

1023
01:09:44,736 --> 01:09:46,800
I've never said a word
about you having a boyfriend.

1024
01:09:46,800 --> 01:09:48,319
But please, choose better.

1025
01:09:48,319 --> 01:09:50,022
- Where'd you even find this thug?
- Who are you calling a thug?

1026
01:09:52,384 --> 01:09:53,216
Hey, calm down.

1027
01:09:53,585 --> 01:09:54,891
Dad.

1028
01:09:56,640 --> 01:09:57,408
Wait.

1029
01:09:57,901 --> 01:09:58,681
Singto.

1030
01:09:59,328 --> 01:09:59,968
Uh.

1031
01:10:00,129 --> 01:10:01,506
It's okay, son. It's okay.

1032
01:10:01,620 --> 01:10:03,323
Come here. It's alright.

1033
01:10:05,367 --> 01:10:06,687
I'll be watching, mom.

1034
01:10:07,113 --> 01:10:10,009
If you stopped paying him,
how long would he stay?

1035
01:10:14,268 --> 01:10:16,326
Wayu, can you listen to me first?

1036
01:10:16,482 --> 01:10:18,271
Let it go. Stay out of it.

1037
01:10:18,271 --> 01:10:19,903
Let it go, you arrogant brat.

1038
01:10:21,053 --> 01:10:22,615
Easy. You're grabbing me too hard. Jeez.

1039
01:10:52,352 --> 01:10:57,312
(Favorite)

1040
01:10:57,312 --> 01:11:01,088
(Tai Moonlit, Foei Moonlit)

1041
01:11:01,088 --> 01:11:05,152
(Richy Moonlit, Kenji Moonlit)

1042
01:11:11,290 --> 01:11:12,866
Hey, stop! This is the police.

1043
01:11:12,866 --> 01:11:13,632
Hands up.

1044
01:11:13,760 --> 01:11:14,304
Turn around.

1045
01:11:14,304 --> 01:11:15,360
- Grab him!
- It's the police.

1046
01:11:16,032 --> 01:11:16,608
After him!

1047
01:11:16,841 --> 01:11:17,984
Stop!

1048
01:11:19,439 --> 01:11:20,404
Who are you?

1049
01:11:20,404 --> 01:11:21,767
Who are you guys?

1050
01:11:22,304 --> 01:11:22,816
Let go.

1051
01:11:22,860 --> 01:11:24,790
Who are you to arrest me?

1052
01:11:24,790 --> 01:11:25,952
Let me go! Let go!

1053
01:11:25,984 --> 01:11:26,592
Stop.

1054
01:11:27,544 --> 01:11:29,730
You're a suspect
in a drug trafficking case.

1055
01:11:30,184 --> 01:11:31,490
You have the right to remain silent.

1056
01:11:31,803 --> 01:11:33,293
Anything you say

1057
01:11:33,307 --> 01:11:35,082
will be used against you
in a court of law.

1058
01:11:36,004 --> 01:11:36,771
So...

1059
01:11:37,027 --> 01:11:38,105
Keep your mouth shut.

1060
01:11:39,014 --> 01:11:39,937
Sergeant, take him away.

1061
01:11:40,618 --> 01:11:41,186
Move.

1062
01:11:41,186 --> 01:11:43,628
- Darn it, let me go! I'm not going!
- Move.

1063
01:11:43,628 --> 01:11:44,593
I'm not going.

1064
01:11:44,593 --> 01:11:46,012
Do you know who I am?

1065
01:11:46,012 --> 01:11:48,384
Let go! Darn it, let go! Let me go!

1066
01:11:48,384 --> 01:11:50,711
Let go! Let me go! Let go!

1067
01:11:51,364 --> 01:11:52,288
Search the whole place.

1068
01:11:52,320 --> 01:11:52,992
Yes, sir.

1069
01:11:53,408 --> 01:11:54,368
Let me go.

1070
01:12:12,714 --> 01:12:16,032
(If you're free, could you come see me?)

1071
01:12:39,074 --> 01:12:39,954
Is it here?

1072
01:12:45,775 --> 01:12:47,875
Sorry to bother you.

1073
01:12:52,631 --> 01:12:55,214
Not at all. I was free anyway.

1074
01:13:02,426 --> 01:13:03,803
If something's wrong, you can tell me.

1075
01:13:05,123 --> 01:13:06,471
We're in the same boat now.

1076
01:13:22,200 --> 01:13:23,619
In that case...

1077
01:13:28,559 --> 01:13:30,575
Could you take me and Singto in?

1078
01:13:32,931 --> 01:13:34,237
I have nowhere else to go.

1079
01:13:45,551 --> 01:13:46,261
Of course.

1080
01:13:50,008 --> 01:13:51,087
Don't worry.

1081
01:13:52,436 --> 01:13:54,012
I'll take care of you and Singto.

1082
01:13:57,546 --> 01:13:58,228
It's okay.

1083
01:14:28,544 --> 01:14:33,318
♪I love you with all my heart,
and I'm ready to give you everything♪

1084
01:14:33,574 --> 01:14:37,833
♪All one life can offer♪

1085
01:14:38,272 --> 01:14:43,421
♪I won't leave you behind,
no matter what I face♪

1086
01:14:43,421 --> 01:14:46,441
♪No matter how bad♪

1087
01:14:46,720 --> 01:14:51,580
♪I give you my all,
my body and everything♪

1088
01:14:51,580 --> 01:14:56,083
♪Please trust your life
with someone like me♪

1089
01:14:56,332 --> 01:15:01,157
♪I assure you there's no one♪

1090
01:15:01,173 --> 01:15:06,624
♪Could ever love you more than I do♪

1091
01:15:14,396 --> 01:15:18,368
♪Like a poem, heartache♪

1092
01:15:18,560 --> 01:15:22,974
♪Won't stay with us for long,
but will slowly fade away♪

1093
01:15:23,363 --> 01:15:27,713
♪You came into my life
and carried me away♪

1094
01:15:28,514 --> 01:15:31,726
♪To something I never expected♪

1095
01:15:32,135 --> 01:15:36,633
♪To truly understand
a love beyond reason♪

1096
01:15:36,928 --> 01:15:41,164
♪When I found someone like you♪

1097
01:15:41,440 --> 01:15:45,933
♪My whole life no longer
has to keep dreaming♪

1098
01:15:46,507 --> 01:15:49,842
♪Now that you're right here♪

1099
01:15:50,183 --> 01:15:54,633
♪I love you with all my heart,
and I'm ready to give it all♪

1100
01:15:55,020 --> 01:15:59,230
